{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS-1 REVIEW (G6 — approach soundness, anti-patterns & alternative-selection) on the \"Repo-snapshot isolation for code-reading gates\" plan. Grounded against src/rebar/signing.py and src/rebar/_commands/transition.py. Confirms the prior G6 pass's central seam finding (re-verified live).\n\nAFFIRMATIONS: snapshot materialization mechanism (object-store read, no worktree, read-tree+checkout-index over lossy git archive); concurrency/atomicity model (atomic dir-rename, single-flight, delete-on-last-close); attested/local structural separation that bars the named footgun; positive rationale grounded in mainstream practice — all sound and well-specified for G6. See structured findings JSON for the load-bearing signing-seam under-specification."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782519591410073001,"uuid":"60e06b7b-9772-46c2-8407-40006f41e45d"}